<paragraph id="F31C3696CC10FFD52680FE7DFA916CF0" blockId="1.[151,1436,405,466]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
FEMALE (
<figureCitation id="6B982A13CC10FFD5270EFE7EFE606C8C" box="[281,392,405,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,521,1860]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[161,1446,521,1868]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Megachile disjuncta female: 1. habitus dorsal view; 2. head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 3. wing; 4. metasoma, dorsal view; 5. sterna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226068/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Figs. 
<number id="456B24B1CC10FFD5274BFE7EFE606C8C" box="[348,392,405,430]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC10FFD527B6FE7EFDF36C8C" bold="true" box="[417,539,405,430]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by its pubescence. Face and tibia are with black, hypostome, vertex and first abdominal segment with pale white and pollen scopa with black pubescence.
</paragraph>
<caption id="A7DC661ECC10FFD52680F8B6FE176AB0" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226068/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" targetBox="[161,1436,521,1860]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC10FFD52680F8B6FE176AB0" blockId="1.[151,1436,1885,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC10FFD52680F8B6FED16A51" bold="true" box="[151,313,1885,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">FIGURES 1–5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="34A34D15CC10FFD52728F8B6FDE56A51" box="[319,525,1885,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC10FFD52728F8B6FDE56A51" box="[319,525,1885,1907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Megachile disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female: 1. habitus dorsal view; 2. head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 3. wing; 4. metasoma, dorsal view; 5. sterna, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="A7DC661ECC13FFD62680F9FBFD7F6B67" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" targetBox="[151,1436,193,1529]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC13FFD62680F9FBFD7F6B67" blockId="2.[151,1436,1552,1605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC13FFD62680F9FBFEAD6B04" bold="true" box="[151,325,1552,1575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">FIGURES 6–11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="34A34D15CC13FFD6275CF9FAFDF06B05" box="[331,536,1553,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC13FFD6275CF9FAFDF06B05" box="[331,536,1553,1575]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Megachile disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male: 6. habitus, dorsal view; 7. head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 8. wing; 9. metasoma, dorsal view; 10. sterna, ventral view; 11. genitalia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC13FFD626D0F984FD7A6A35" blockId="2.[151,1437,1647,2032]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC13FFD626D0F984FEF86BAA" bold="true" box="[199,272,1647,1672]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Head:</emphasis>
Clypeus elevated medially, punctures coarse and close; supraclypeus slightly elevated; parocular area sloping laterally below level of antennae; carina distinct; subocellar area broadly convex, median groove obscure; mandibles broad at apex, the outer tooth acute; vertex broad, flattish, produced black; the back of head roundly emarginated; lateral ocelli nearer eye and each other than to occipital margin and nearer eye than to each other; vestibule reaching up to mid coxae in repose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC13FFD626D0F8C8FDE66AD2" blockId="2.[151,1437,1647,2032]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC13FFD626D0F8C8FEA66A1E" bold="true" box="[199,334,1827,1852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Mesosoma:</emphasis>
Scutum convex, striated, median and parapsidal lines distinct, pronotal lobes swollen but incarinate, punctures dense; scutellum broadly rounded posteriorly, nearly horizontal in profile; apex acute, median length longer than median groove but less than twice its length; first recurrent vein far from base than second which is close to apex of second submarginal cell, wing hyaline at base fuscous towards apex, veins black; forelegs coxae, trochanter simple, outer face closely punctate, anterior and posterior face smooth, apices of tarsi slightly excavated; hind legs simple and unmodified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC12FFD726D0FF7CFCB16C3F" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis id="C1D7EA84CC12FFD726D0FF7CFEA56D92" bold="true" box="[199,333,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">Metasoma:</emphasis>
Basal tergal concavity margin incarinate, pregrandular area narrowly shining along upper margin otherwise finely and closely punctate, vertical fold linear, postgrandular area short, slightly convex medially; graduli of terga 
<number id="456B24B1CC12FFD72744FF34FE956DDA" box="[339,381,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
complete and linear, punctures coarse and close becoming crowded; basal sternum slightly elevated medially; graduli of sterna 
<number id="456B24B1CC12FFD7243DFEEFFDBD6C3F" box="[554,597,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
linear and subcarinate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC12FFD726D0FEC3FEEB6C8E" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
MALE (
<figureCitation id="6B982A13CC12FFD7273EFECCFE4E6C62" box="[297,422,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1529]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 11. Megachile disjuncta male: 6. habitus, dorsal view; 7. head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 8. wing; 9. metasoma, dorsal view; 10. sterna, ventral view; 11. genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
Figs. 
<number id="456B24B1CC12FFD7277CFECCFE4E6C62" box="[363,422,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594" value="8.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="6.0">6–11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slightly convex, closely and finely punctate, apical margin notched medially, base, sides and apex of clypeus with long white pubescence; mandibles tridentate, apical tooth acute, lower surface without any process; fore coxae with short but acute spine, trochanters longer than broad, punctures close and fine on coxae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F31C3696CC12FFD726D0FE5CFDE76CD6" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="594">
